They say good things come to those who wait so we held off on this booking for the off-chance that the ever fabulous Philipp Jung would extend his west coast visit to play this Tutu Tuesday--and we won!

It is not easy to pin down this globetrotting DJ demigod but he is feeling the Burning Man vibes and we are about to Get extremely Physical at Harlot this month.

There is an air of mystery shrouding the true meaning behind the acronym of M.A.N.D.Y., an alias which embodies the mutual talents of childhood friends Philipp Jung and Patrick Bodmer. The pair readily indulge this curiosity by toying with various clever possibilities, including Me AND You, but the truth is likely a giggle under each of their talented breaths. P and P have carved a unique niche in electronic music by consistently selecting productions that induce their audience into a somatic frenzy. On the platform of their aptly titled Get Physical label, M.A.N.D.Y. has achieved massive success in colluding to create music that simply makes bodies move. Their foot stamping, hair flying passion is the ultimate expression of a dance music phenomenon for many years.

When M.A.N.D.Y. and Booka Shade joined as musical soul mates with DJ T., first in Frankfurt, then in Berlin, Get Physical produced a caliber of electricity that rippled throughout the EDM community and into the relative mainstream. Philipp's charm and savvy, Patrick's allusive artistry, DJ T.'s killer entrepreneurial sense and Booka Shade's collaborative genius combined to form a masterpiece of intelligent design that reflects romantic sensibility and technical virtuosity. Together, they push the boundaries of dance music to compile an enviable arsenal of electro kissing house while caressing disco and flirting with techno. Body Language was the ubiquitous hit of 2005 and M.A.N.D.Y.'s Fabric Series three years later cemented their reputation as two of the most captivating selectors on the planet. One of their most recent prestige was a complication for Renaissance in 2009 which was met with tremendous accolades and described by Resident Advisor as "maturity, smarts, and cohesion...that is rare these days."

Philipp and Patrick know exactly which buttons to press to make that bass jiggle up your spine and seduce your body free. Alongside many lives compadres Booka Shade, M.A.N.D.Y. has taken some time from their hectic global tour schedule to devise new elaborations, culminating in the release of Body Language Vol. 10 in April 2011. In addition to a single release that will be the first Booka Shade vs. M.A.N.D.Y. cooperation to be heard in years, the boys have closed on a revolutionary touring show that utilizes infrared technology and a new mapping technique to project inverted video effects onto their Physical form as they perform. It is no doubt that their plans for this never before seen live visual component will conjure the kind of visceral excitement that only this duo can. In the feat of the imagination, M.A.N.D.Y. powers on through a perpetual rebirth into pulsating beats and pretty lights.

-Carla Tutu

ENVELOP is a 3D immersive music venue (28.4 ambisonic system) with interactive lights and video, to be installed in The Midway a creative complex opening soon in the Dogpatch district of SF. Using software we've developed, artists can seamlessly compose music that will envelop the listener with sound that moves around the audience from any direction. We believe this is the future of music production. We have currently raised enough funding for the equipment but need the community's support for the final build out.  Help us launch our Kickstarter campaign so together we can make this vision a reality!

Thursday, April 9th 
8:00 PM - 1:00 AM
Public Works, San Francisco
FREE

Music by Christopher Willits (DJ Set), Mikey Maramag DJ set (Blackbird Blackbird) DJ Dials, Manitous, Mophono (DJ Set), and other special guests!

+ Head's up that this is a stereo (normal 2 channel) event using Public Works wonderful Funktion-One system. 
In other words, we need to raise the money for the 3D ENVELOP experience!

About ENVELOP:

An intimate performance space opening Summer 2015 and housed within The Midway creative complex in San Francisco, ENVELOP is at once a unique audiovisual instrument for electronic artists, and a world-class venue for audiences to experience sound and light.

Designed from the ground up for immersive electronic music and performance, the ENVELOP system comprises a next-generation 28.4 channel Ambisonic sound system, individually addressable LED lights, and high-definition video projection. The entire audiovisual system can be controlled as a single instrument using open-source software that integrates into an electronic musician or lighting artist's existing toolkit.

Broad Street Food Truck Crawl with Jorge
properties.desc:
It's summer time, the perfect time to sample all the great food trucks on Broad Street. There is so much great (and inexpensive) food from so many cultures among these local businesses, so let's go out and experience as much of it as we possibly can!

We will convene at the famous Johnny's Chimi truck (986 Broad St., between Sumter and Gallatin), and proceed down Broad Street, stopping and sampling along the way. This is a casual, informal, and family friendly gathering. Join us for one truck or several – just be sure to arrive hungry! 

PLEASE NOTE: This is not a fundraiser or official campaign event. Attendance will not be interpreted as a formal endorsement of our campaign. We just want to break bread with you – and support small local businesses together.

-----
Recorrido de Visita a los Camiones de comida de Broad Street con Jorge 

Llegó el verano, la época perfecta para saborear las comidas de los camiones en Broad Street. Hay tanta variedad de comida (y a bajos precios) de muchas culturas en estos negocios. ¡Así es que vamos a salir y experimentar con cuantas variedades nos sea posible! 

Nos vamos a reunir en el famoso camión Johnny's Chimi (986 Broad St., entre las calles Sumter y Gallatin), y enfilaremos a lo largo de Broad Street, deteniéndonos y probando comidas en los diferentes camiones. Esta es una actividad familiar informal. Acompáñennos a visitar uno o más camiones. ¡Solo asegúrense de llegar hambrientos! 

NOTA: Esto no es una recaudación de fondos ni un evento oficial de la campaña. La asistencia no debiera ser interpretada como un apoyo formal a nuestra campaña. Solamente queremos cortar pan con usted y, al mismo tiempo, apoyar a nuestros pequeños negocios.

Join us for three days of festivities celebrating all things handmade! More than 225 top contemporary jewelry, clothing, furniture, and home décor artists from across the country will gather under one roof. More info on the DANCE WORKSHOP: 
Through this transformational playshop, we will explore the language of dance. We will explore how we convey this magic into a conversation that moves us into deeper connection with each other and our dance. We will play with what sets apart just another dance from really communicating in dialects you may not even have known you spoke and creating those dances that you remember through time. Feel free to send them to me, or post them on the event wall. 

Looking forward to celebrating with you all in a few short months!

The event is public so you can invite select people you think will be a positive addition to my life and the lives of my friends and people I love and care about.

Chat with the crew to hear about their experience building the catacomb. We are about 61% of our fundraising goal. At 220' across and covering almost 19,000 square feet of playa area, Catacomb of Veils will be the largest art piece at Burning Man 2016 and one of the largest burned sculptures in the history of the event. Everyone participating in the creation of Catacomb is all-volunteer with a commitment to the transformative power of temporary art. Our community of artists and builders is so grateful for your contribution and support. 

Catacomb rises like a rocky outcropping off the desert floor, and as the dust swirls up and around, it evokes Black Rock Point itself. It is a ruin of a previous society-- a remnant of our collective search for moments of quiet, introspection and reflection. It is a journey of discovery and a descent into a subterranean world. Explore with us.

properties.name: Technology and Your Brain Part 2
properties.desc:
If you did not attend part 1, no problem!  Dr. Chung will provide a brief review of part 1 and then begin the therapeutic applications for balancing the body and the brain.

Living in a 24/7 technologically wired society is literally re-wiring our brains.

Do you have some type of glowing screen in front of you for all or most of the day?  Do you work in front of a computer, check your smartphone when you’re at lunch, and then turn a computer or TV screen (or both) on at night?  

Are you aware of a sense of imbalance between your mind and body?  Do you feel anxious, restless or easily distracted?  Are you finding that you are developing digestive, physical, or emotional problems?  Do you want to improve both your mental and physical performance?

In this class we will discuss the influence of technology on the neurological development and function of the brain, and how to create balance for long-term health and wellness.   

Rachman Chung< DC, DACNB, FACFN
Board Certified Chiropractic Neurologist
Fellow of the American College of Functional Neurology
Rachman Chung is a chiropractic neurologist and natural medicine practitioner.  He specializes in sport and spine injuries and complex neurological conditions ranging from balance and movement problems, learning and behavior disorders and neurodegenerative diseases, such as Alzheimer's, Parkinson's and dementia. As a chiropractic neurologist he looks at the impact the environment has upon human development in health and disease, and utilizes the latest advances in laboratory techniques to measure early bio-markers of disease.
 
Dr. Chung is a former extreme athlete. He knows from personal experience what it is like to suffer from chronic injury and the level of commitment necessary to fully recover. Dr. Chung graduated from Palmer College of Chiropractic West, cum laude.

Prior to becoming a chiropractor, Dr. Chung was a high-level competitive skateboarder. He was sponsored by several companies (including: Powell Peralta, Airwalk shoes, Venture trucks and others) and appeared in international videos and magazines. While on the verge of reaching his professional goals, recurrent injuries ended his career. With the help of chiropractic and alternative medicine Dr. Chung restored his physical health and became inspired to do the same for others. At present, he is actively learning dance, cycling and kite surfing.

This class is free. Come as you are!

properties.name: FREEDOM! in San Francisco

results.formatted_address: 909 Tennessee St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA

properties.desc:
Thanks to Wayne de Geere III, The American Campfire FREEDOM! Tour, also known as the "Adam Kokesh Avoids His Probation Officer Tour" is coming to the city of his birth! Adam has been using his book as an excuse to travel the country talking about freedom, winning converts, happiness, and psychedelics. He'll have free books and stickers available for everyone.

FREEDOM!
The wisdom within these pages has the power to unlock our potential as a species and establish an enduring civilization based on peace, self-ownership, and nonviolence.

You, as a free, beautiful, independent human being with inalienable rights, own yourself! You can do what you want with your own body and the product of your labor. All human interactions should be free of force and coercion, and we are free to exercise our rights, limited only by respect for the rights of others. Governments rely on force, and force is a poor substitute for persuasion. When you learned “don’t hit,” “don’t steal,” and “don’t kill,” it wasn’t, “unless you work for the government.” Governments frighten us into thinking we need them, but we are moving past the statist paradigm and rendering them obsolete.

This book will empower YOU to be more happy, free, and prosperous, while putting you in a position to help shape our destiny.

Adam Kokesh joined the US Marines at age 17 and volunteered for combat duty in Iraq in 2004. This critical experience showed him that war is a racket and led him to deeply question his most cherished statist beliefs. He first rose to fame as an anti-war activist before branching out into other areas, often taking action too risky for other activists. In 2010, he became an independent journalist as ADAM VS THE MAN. He has been arrested and gone to jail dozens of times standing up for his convictions. He began writing FREEDOM! while caged in Washington, DC. While he has inspired millions with his speeches, videos, and civil disobedience, his greatest contribution to the cause of freedom is the concept of localization as a way to overcome statism and achieving a free world. To learn more, please go to thefreedomline.com.

Paul A. Pritchett

700 NE 30th Ave.
Ocala, Fl 34474
